snippet.textDisplay: I also have a 13B turbo mini van, it’s a white Suzuki carry van on YouTube and there are a few videos floating around of it. I have used a manual gearbox out of a bigger van as I had planned on running it N/A so I could get it engineered for street use. Since doing work on it I changed my mind and have now decided to turbo it and have done all the appropriate things to get it passed so I can still use it for street use with the turbo. I found that the seat height was the biggest issue I had. I will be making a custom intake manifold and have had a few people ask me to make me an intake manifold for them so I may do that if I feel up to it. I like how you guys are not scared to show your welds ha ha ha ha....keep on posting them videos mate.
